reviews.review_text: Boston Fall '91 N3 Shakedown opener followed by CCR into the rarely played Train to Cry. Played only seven times: once in '73, six times in '91, and the final version 3/16/92. Novelty, I guess, that I don't particularly love, but it's sweet in the first set. Another rarity pops up in the second set: First Nobody's Fault since '85. That's a whopping 450 show gap. Next played 144 shows later on 12/12/93, then retired after the final version just over a year later (88 show gap) on 12/19/94. It's only a couple minutes, coming out of He's Gone, then segues with ease into Spoonful. Another excellent Pearson/Healy Board recently uploaded to the archive. To be honest, I'm more enamored by the audio quality than the actual music. Post-Brent dueling pianos - not my favorite era. But these Spaces are better than I recall. Also dig the symphonic LIG and the Stella Blue. Lovely Heaven’s Door to send everyone off.

Best Show of the Run IMO one of the best shows of '91. Energy is just right, especially for the first 2/3 of the show. This Shakedown was my introduction into '91 Dead and it's a killer. Check it all out + Christopher Hazard has videos on YT as well
